<paragraph blockId="23.[151,885,1764,1786]" box="[151,885,1764,1786]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Type species 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker, 1910: 54" authorityName="Becker" authorityPageNumber="54" authorityYear="1910" box="[287,739,1764,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Phyladelphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thalhammeri">
<emphasis box="[287,560,1764,1786]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Phyladelphus thalhammeri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[566,704,1764,1786]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref41190" refString="Becker, T. (1910) Chloropidae. Eine monographische Studie. 2. Teil. Aethiopische Region. Annales historico-naturales Musei nationalis hungarici Budapest, 8, 377 - 443, tab. XIII." type="journal article">Becker, 1910</bibRefCitation>
: 54
</taxonomicName>
by monotypy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,1830,2035]" lastBlockId="24.[151,1436,151,392]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Left unattributed to a genus group by 
<bibRefCitation box="[573,834,1830,1855]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref41065" refString="Andersson, H. (1977) Taxonomic and phylogenetic studies on Chloropidae (Diptera) with special reference to Old World genera. In: Entomologica scandinavica. 8 (Supplement). Scandinavian Science Press, Klampenborg, pp. 1 - 200." type="book chapter">Andersson (1977: 180)</bibRefCitation>
, this genus is known from two oriental, one European and one 
<collectingRegion box="[247,295,1867,1890]" country="Cameroon" name="East" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">East</collectingRegion>
African species. Notes on it are given by 
<bibRefCitation box="[769,1069,1866,1891]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref41720" refString="Deeming, J. C. (1981) A contribution to the study of afrotropical Chloropine Diptera. Journal of Natural History, 15 (5), 789 - 828. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222938100770581" type="journal article">Deeming (1981: 811–812)</bibRefCitation>
, who was only able to liken it to 
<taxonomicName authority="Speiser, 1910" authorityName="Speiser" authorityYear="1910" box="[151,481,1902,1927]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Mepachymerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,322,1902,1927]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Mepachymerus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[329,481,1902,1927]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref43150" refString="Speiser, P. (1910) [Abteilung] 10. Diptera. 5. Cyclorhapha [sic!], Aschiza. Cyclorhapha, Schizophora, Schizometopa. (Auswahl); Holometopa. (Auswahl). In: Koniglich schwedische Akademie der Wissenschaften (Ed.), Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der schwedischen zoologischen Expedition nach dem Kilimandjaro, dem Meru und den umgebenden Massaisteppen Deutsch-Ostafrikas 1905 - 1906 unter Leitung von Prof. Dr. Yngve Sjostedt. 2. Band, Abteilung 8 - 14. P. Palmquists Aktiebolag, Stockholm, pp. 113 - 202 incl. index." type="book chapter">Speiser, 1910</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
which latter 
<bibRefCitation box="[630,889,1902,1927]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref41065" refString="Andersson, H. (1977) Taxonomic and phylogenetic studies on Chloropidae (Diptera) with special reference to Old World genera. In: Entomologica scandinavica. 8 (Supplement). Scandinavian Science Press, Klampenborg, pp. 1 - 200." type="book chapter">Andersson (1977: 132)</bibRefCitation>
placed along with 
<taxonomicName authority="Frey, 1961" authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1961" box="[1104,1386,1902,1927]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Steleocerellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1104,1259,1902,1927]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Steleocerellus</emphasis>
Frey, 
<quantity box="[1330,1386,1902,1927]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.98094" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="in" value="1961.0">1961</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in a discrete genus group. 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker, 1910" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1910" box="[403,685,1938,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Phyladelphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geminus">
<emphasis box="[403,525,1940,1963]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">P. geminus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[534,685,1938,1963]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref41190" refString="Becker, T. (1910) Chloropidae. Eine monographische Studie. 2. Teil. Aethiopische Region. Annales historico-naturales Musei nationalis hungarici Budapest, 8, 377 - 443, tab. XIII." type="journal article">Becker, 1910</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and the new species here described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deeming" authorityYear="2018" box="[1138,1235,1938,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Phyladelphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="woodi">
<emphasis box="[1138,1235,1938,1963]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">P. woodi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have in common with this genus group a flattened laceolate arista that is often rather rounded apically and which is clothed in very short setae. However, such aristal development does occur elsewhere. Duda (1933: 142) described a 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Steleocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindbergi">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Steleocerus lindbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[326,427,152,175]" name="Morocco" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Morocco</collectingCountry>
with just such aristal development (
<taxonomicName authority="Becker, 1910" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1910" box="[848,1136,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Steleocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[848,976,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Steleocerus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[986,1136,151,176]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref41190" refString="Becker, T. (1910) Chloropidae. Eine monographische Studie. 2. Teil. Aethiopische Region. Annales historico-naturales Musei nationalis hungarici Budapest, 8, 377 - 443, tab. XIII." type="journal article">Becker, 1910</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is now placed as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Speiser" authorityName="Speiser" authorityYear="1910" box="[296,558,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Mepachymerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[296,467,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Mepachymerus</emphasis>
Speiser
</taxonomicName>
of the same year). This species was recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1159,1255,188,213]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
and transferred into 
<taxonomicName authority="Becker" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1910" box="[205,405,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Lasiosina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[205,314,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Lasiosina</emphasis>
Becker
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation box="[455,763,223,248]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref41334" refString="Beschovski, V. (1983) On the systematic status of Steleocerus lindbergi (Duda, 1933) (Diptera, Chloropidae). Acta zoologica bulgarica, 21, 78 - 82. [Zoological Record translation of title in Bulgarian]" type="journal article">Beschovski (1983: 78–80)</bibRefCitation>
. My dissection of the abdomen of a female from 
<collectingCountry box="[1356,1436,223,248]" name="Turkey" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(Ödemis, Lake Gölcük, 
<date box="[421,536,260,285]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1997-07-09">9.vii.1997</date>
, J.C. Deeming, in 
<collectionCode box="[744,836,260,284]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/e7dr-nxad" name="National Museum of Wales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">NMWC</collectionCode>
) confirms this. It has narrow cerci and the ovipositor, when extended, is nearly as long as the abdomen. Thus, in the 
<taxonomicName box="[881,1023,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chloropidae</taxonomicName>
, the character of a blade-like arista, which is undoubtedly apomorphic and cannot be regarded as being of diagnostic significance in the attributing of species to genera, although in the 
<taxonomicName box="[531,670,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Lauxaniidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lauxaniidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[724,851,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Celyphidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Celyphidae</taxonomicName>
it may well be so.
</paragraph>
